Title: LLM-Powered Engineering Intelligence System for Bug Analysis & Failure Prediction

Overview: 
This project is an AI-powered engineering assistant that analyzes software failures using LLMs, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), and Machine Learning.

It helps developers and QA engineers identify root causes, assess risk, and generate test strategies automatically.

Features:
- Root cause analysis from logs, bugs, and code
- Risk prediction using ML model (Logistic Regression)
- RAG-based knowledge retrieval (FAISS)
- Structured debugging output (Root cause, Risk, Test cases)
- Real-time metrics (latency, retrieval score, response quality)
- Interactive UI (Streamlit)

Architecture:
User Query
   ↓
Frontend (Streamlit)
   ↓
FastAPI Backend
   ↓
RAG Pipeline (FAISS + Embeddings)
   ↓
LLM (Reasoning Engine)
   ↓
ML Model (Risk Prediction)
   ↓
Response + Metrics

Example Output:
Query: Why is Payment API slow?

Root Cause: Database timeout during peak traffic  
Risk Level: Critical  
Suggested Tests:
- Load testing under peak traffic
- Query optimization validation
- Timeout threshold testing

Metrics:

- Latency (sec)
- Retrieval Accuracy
- Response Quality Score
- Risk Prediction Confidence

Tech Stack:
- Python, FastAPI
- Streamlit
- FAISS (Vector DB)
- OpenAI / LLM
- Scikit-learn (ML)
- Docker (optional)
- Render (Deployment)

Future Improvements:
- Multi-agent architecture
- Graph-based debugging
- Real-time log ingestion
- CI/CD integration

